0.04  2026-05-27
    - Fix ABA race in slot_acquire's per-slot recovery: a recoverer racing
      a fresh free+acquire cycle could clobber a live owner because both
      acquisitions present identical state (RESP_ACQUIRED). Now claims
      exclusive recovery via owner_pid CAS dead->0 first (mirrors Pool's
      recover_stale fix); state and owner_pid loads use ACQUIRE.
    - Fix reply TOCTOU on generation: between gen check and state CAS, a
      cancel + re-acquire could recycle the slot, letting reply stamp READY
      onto a wrong owner's slot (which would then read the wrong data).
      Now re-checks gen before CAS and recovers post-CAS by bumping gen +
      resetting state.
    - Fix size() snapshot wrap: reading tail before head could underflow
      to a huge value if a consumer increments head between the loads.
      Read head first; clamp result to 0 if tail < head.
    - Plug mmap/fd leak when reqrep_setup_handle calloc fails in
      create_int / create_int_memfd paths.
    - Harden validate_header: reject files where resp_stride is too small
      to hold full slot data area (prevents replies overflowing into next
      slot's header on a crafted file).
    - Fix slot_release ABA: two-step CAS (owner_pid mypid->0, then state
      from_known->FREE) so a fresh owner's slot isn't blindly clobbered
      when clear()/recovery race the release path (was incorrect for both
      try_get's READY release and try_send-failure's ACQUIRED release).
    - compute_layout: resp_stride was computed in uint32, which wrapped to
      a tiny value for resp_data_max near UINT32_MAX (replies would then
      overflow into neighboring slots). Compute in uint64 and reject if
      stride exceeds uint32 range.


